=== Key Interpretations ===

1. MINIMUM DETECTABLE EFFECTS (80% power, alpha=0.05):
   Rajasthan 2005-2010: MDE = 2.8 pp (30% of control mean 9.2%)

   Rajasthan 2010-2015: MDE = 2.9 pp (32% of control mean 8.8%)

   Rajasthan 2015-2020: MDE = 3.3 pp (27% of control mean 12.1%)

   Rajasthan 2005-2020 (LT): MDE = 4.0 pp (35% of control mean 11.2%)

   UP 2005-2010: MDE = 1.7 pp (12% of control mean 14.8%)

   UP 2010-2015: MDE = 1.9 pp (12% of control mean 16.0%)

   UP 2015-2021: MDE = 1.9 pp (11% of control mean 17.4%)

   UP 2005-2021 (LT): MDE = 1.9 pp (10% of control mean 19.2%)


2. WHAT WE CAN RULE OUT (upper bound of 95% CI):
   Rajasthan 2005-2010: Can rule out effects > 3.4 pp (37% increase from 9.2%)

   Rajasthan 2010-2015: Can rule out effects > -0.8 pp (-9% increase from 8.8%)

   Rajasthan 2015-2020: Can rule out effects > 2.8 pp (23% increase from 12.1%)

   Rajasthan 2005-2020 (LT): Can rule out effects > 5.9 pp (52% increase from 11.2%)

   UP 2005-2010: Can rule out effects > 2.3 pp (15% increase from 14.8%)

   UP 2010-2015: Can rule out effects > 3.0 pp (19% increase from 16.0%)

   UP 2015-2021: Can rule out effects > 5.8 pp (33% increase from 17.4%)

   UP 2005-2021 (LT): Can rule out effects > 1.7 pp (9% increase from 19.2%)


3. COMPARISON TO BHAVNANI (2009):
   Bhavnani found ~15pp effect (5x increase from ~3% baseline)
   Our precision allows detecting effects as small as:
   - Rajasthan: 2.8-3.3 pp

   - UP: 1.7-1.9 pp

   We would detect a Bhavnani-sized effect with >99% power.

